        title: "Why don't boys get periods?",
        content:
          "Boys don't get periods because their bodies are different to girls'! \r\n\r\nGirls' bodies do things like produce eggs, provide a place for a fertilized egg (or baby) to grow, and have periods. Boys' bodies produce sperm, and release fluid with sperm in it (called semen) to fertilize eggs.",
        category: 'Boys, men and relationships',
