        title: 'When does puberty start?',
        content:
          'For most girls, puberty starts between the ages of 9–13, but it can be earlier or later. \r\n\r\nEveryone goes through puberty differently. The first change girls will notice is breast growth, often on one side first. \r\n\r\nBoys start puberty a little later than girls, usually between 10–14 years old.',
        category: 'Puberty',
